text: Pseudebulea kuatunensis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Munroe and Mutuura in 1968. It is found in China (Fujian, Hubei). ==Subspecies== *Pseudebulea kuatunensis kuatunensis (China: Fujian) *Pseudebulea kuatunensis ichangensis Munroe & Mutuura, 1968 (China: Hubei) ==References== Category:Moths described in 1968 Category:Pyraustinae
title: Pseudebulea kuatunensis
